<tt><font size="2">7. THE STANDARDS OF ADMINISTRATION</font></tt>
<p><tt><font size="2">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;In comparing the various methods from the standpoint of</font></tt><br>
<tt><font size="2">administration, it is necessary to ask several specific, narrow</font></tt><br>
<tt><font size="2">questions, and this is done in Table D [see below].</font></tt>
<p><tt><font size="2">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;TABLE D</font></tt><br>
<tt><font size="2">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;STANDARDS OF ADMINISTRATION</font></tt><br>
<tt><font size="2">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;(YES indicates an advantage) (NO indicates a disadvantage)</font></tt><br>
